name: Momma Iquana's Fresh Vegetabel Chili
keywords: beans, vegetables, dairy-free, gluten-free, high fiber, low cholesterol, nut-free, vegan, vegetarian, fall, winter, main course
recipeIngredient: 1 cup red pepper cored, seeded and cut in 1-inch cubes
2 cups cooked pinto or kidney beans
4 cups crushed fresh or canned, drained tomatoes
1/2 cup very mild pure chili powder (see note)

recipeInstructions.text: Saute onions and celery in hot oil until soft.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes.
